README for witek: (12/10/99) Packaged w/ GVS v4/14

2A-53-w uses Witek Krajewski's algorithm.  This package contains

the following executable files, documentation, and data files:

  Executable files:
  ----------------
  * 2A-53-w - The perl script, the front end to Witek's algorithm program.
	          This produces product for one hour-granule.
  * singlevos_2A-53-w - The perl script, the front end to Witek's 
              algorithm program. This produces product for a single VOS.
  * rainest, out.x prep_proc - Actual algorithm programs.

  Documentation:
  -------------
  * 2A-53-w.html - Documentation for 2A-53-w.

  Data files:
  ----------
  * carttopol.{DR|FL} - Lookup tables for converting cartesian to polar 
       coordinates for Darwin and Melbourn data sets.
  * poltocart.{DR|FL} - Lookup tables for converting polar to cartesian 
       coordinates for Darwin and Melbourn data sets.
  * {darw|melb}_rainest.par - Default parameters files for Darwin and 
       Melbourn data sets.



EXECUTION NOTES:
================

You need to:

1. Install lookup tables under $GVS_DATA_PATH; otherwise, specify the pathname
   of the lookup tables when executing '2A-53-w'.

2. Have access to the executable files located in $GVS/format_conversion
   and in this directory.
 



QUESTIONS:
=========

